e sold at St. Paul's Cathedral in London.","jurisdictionLevel":0},{"id":1705206,"age":11,"year":"1571","julianDay":2294856,"title":"The Royal Exchange is Organized","description":"The Royal Exchange was organized in January 1571 by Sir Thomas Gresham. Gresham is known as the father of English banking.","jurisdictionLevel":0},{"id":1705210,"age":40,"year":"1600","julianDay":2305448,"title":"The Honourable East India Company","description":"The Honourable East India Company, a British joint-stock company, was established in 1600 for trade in the Indian Ocean region. At its height, the British East India Company had a private army which was twice the size of the British Army, ruled large sections of India, and revenues in the millions.","url":"https://www.historic-uk.com/HistoryUK/HistoryofEngland/The-East-India-Company/","urlTitle":"Historic UK - The East India Company","jurisdictionLevel":0},{"id":1705212,"age":60,"year":"1620","julianDay":2312753,"title":"The Pilgrims Board the Mayflower","description":"\"The Pilgrims boarded the Mayflower in search of religious freedom in the New World in September 1620. The Mayflower set sail from Plymouth, England, with 102 passengers, 40 of whom called themselves \"\"Saints.\"\" After two stormy months at sea, the ship reached the New World. Nearly half of the group died during their first winter due to malnutrition and the harsh New England winter.\"","url":"https://www.themayflowersociety.org/the-pilgrims/pilgrim-history","urlTitle":"The Mayflower Society - Pilgrim History","jurisdictionLevel":0},{"id":1705213,"age":82,"year":"1642","toYear":"1651","julianDay":2320789,"title":"The English Civil War","description":"A series of conflicts regarding England's governance during the years 1642 to 1651 is now known as The English Civil War. Charles I summoned supporters to join him against his enemies in Parliament. In October 1642, nearly 10,000 men fought for Charles I and chased Parliament across the River Tamar. Fighting continued for years and was finally ended at the Battle of Worcester on September 3, 1651, with a Parliamentarian victory.","jurisdictionLevel":0}],"lifeSummary":"Jone Conias was born about 1560, in England. She married Francis Chamberlain on 26 July 1587, in Walkern, Hertfordshire, England. They were the parents of at least 3 sons and 1 daughter."},"et":{"about 1560–":"umbes 1560–Surnud","1561–1633":"1561–1633","1578–Female":"1578–Surnud","1589–1623":"1589–1623","1589–Male":"1589–Surnud","1589–1676":"1589–1676","1560–Female":"1560–Surnud","1561":"1561","1571":"1571","1560":"1560","26 July 1587":"26. juuli 1587","11 May 1589":"11. mai 1589","1569":"1569","1623":"1623","1578":"1578","1589":"1589","1 January 1589":"1. jaanuar 1589","1600":"1600","1633":"1633","1676":"1676","1642":"1642","1620":"1620","1651":"1651","about 1560":"umbes 1560","Walkern, Hertfordshire, England, United Kingdom":"Walkern, Hertfordshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Walkern, Hertfordshire, England":"Walkern, Hertfordshire, England","Billericay, Essex, England":"Billericay, Essex, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Nottinghamshire, England, United Kingdom":"Nottinghamshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","England":"England","Billericay, Great Burstead, Essex, England":"Great Burstead, Essex, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"about 1560–":"noin 1560–Kuollut","1561–1633":"1561–1633","1578–Female":"1578–Kuollut","1589–1623":"1589–1623","1589–Male":"1589–Kuollut","1589–1676":"1589–1676","1560–Female":"1560–Kuollut","1561":"1561","1571":"1571","1560":"1560","26 July 1587":"26. heinäkuuta 1587","11 May 1589":"11. toukokuuta 1589","1569":"1569","1623":"1623","1578":"1578","1589":"1589","1 January 1589":"1. tammikuuta 1589","1600":"1600","1633":"1633","1676":"1676","1642":"1642","1620":"1620","1651":"1651","about 1560":"noin 1560","Walkern, Hertfordshire, England, United Kingdom":"Walkern, Hertfordshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Walkern, Hertfordshire, England":"Walkern, Hertfordshire, England","Billericay, 